{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":113851,"duration_api_ms":167915,"num_turns":4,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"465d2e16-9f48-4323-9b43-c472875d6202","total_cost_usd":0.5854013000000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":1454,"cache_creation_input_tokens":35009,"cache_read_input_tokens":63145,"output_tokens":1726,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":35009,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":155,"outputTokens":11657,"cacheReadInputTokens":1484463,"cacheCreationInputTokens":62173,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.28460255,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":1454,"outputTokens":1726,"cacheReadInputTokens":63145,"cacheCreationInputTokens":35009,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.30079875,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Both amendments identify real persistence-integrity defects confirmed by code inspection. The completion journal's delimiter-based serialization is vulnerable to legal identifiers containing \", \" since debug_assert! is the only guard and is stripped in release builds, while ProjectId::new/RunId::new accept such values. The lineage append API writes TaskRunEntry verbatim without ensuring milestone_id is populated, even though it receives the authoritative milestone_id as a separate parameter.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-10-a35fc4da","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed by code inspection: render_completion_journal_details (model.rs:347-379) joins fields with a raw \", \" delimiter and guards against delimiter collision only via debug_assert!, which is stripped in release builds. ProjectId::new validates against empty/dot/slash but NOT commas or spaces; RunId::new only validates against empty. A legal identifier like \"foo, bar\" passes construction, serializes ambiguously, and causes split_required (fs.rs:2315-2319) to split at the wrong position during parse. This breaks the round-trip, so repairable_completion_event cannot correctly merge replayed completion events, producing duplicate journal rows instead of idempotent repair. This is a genuine data-corruption bug in the persistence layer."},{"amendment_id":"fr-10-9fd118d3","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed by code inspection: append_task_run (fs.rs:2682-2691) receives milestone_id as a separate parameter but serializes the TaskRunEntry verbatim via serde_json::to_string(entry) without populating entry.milestone_id. The field is Option<String> with serde(default, skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\"), so a None value simply omits it from the NDJSON row. The backfill via get_or_insert_with only happens in read_task_runs_from_path (fs.rs:2530-2532), meaning on-disk data can be incomplete. While current production callers (record_task_run_start) happen to set milestone_id before calling, the public API contract does not enforce this, violating the self-contained-entry invariant. The fix is straightforward: populate entry.milestone_id from the parameter before serialization."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"6097f5e3-ee66-4bd7-b475-74ab2e94c791"}
